\f0\fs52 \cf0 Sumo Collins\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\ql\qnatural

\fs44 \cf0 The name of this supersize, extra-refreshing Tom Collins was inspired by Ken\'92s House of Pancakes in Hilo, Hawaii, where jumbo orders of saimin and loco moco are announced with a gong crash and the staff yelling \'93Sumo!\'94 \'93We don\'92t yell,\'94 said Fort Defiance owner St. John Frizell. \'93Yet.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs40 \cf0 3 ounces gin\
2 1/4 ounces fresh lemon juice\
1 1/2 ounces {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/22/dining/simple-syrup-recipe.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simple syrup}}\
Chilled seltzer\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 1 orange wheel.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\b\fs44 \cf0 Preparation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs40 \cf0 Pour the gin, lemon juice and simple syrup into a cocktail shaker, fill with ice, and shake vigorously. Strain into a 24-ounce glass filled with fresh ice, top with seltzer. Garnish with the orange wheel.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf0 Yield: 1 drink.\

