\f0\fs52 \cf0 Guadalajara Sour\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\ql\qnatural

\fs44 \cf0 The bartender Michael Bowers has taken to garnishing this cocktail with a twist of grapefruit, which he squeezes away from the drink before dropping it in. \'93Grapefruit oil can be really overwhelming,\'94 he said, \'93especially here, where its purpose is to augment the aroma of the ros\'e9, not overtake it.\'94\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs40 \cf0 1 3/4 ounces blanco tequila\
3/4 ounce lemon juice\
3/4 ounce {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/22/dining/simple-syrup-recipe.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simple syrup}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 3/4 ounce chilled ros\'e9.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\b\fs44 \cf0 Preparation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs40 \cf0 Combine the tequila, lemon juice and simple syrup in a cocktail shaker, fill with ice and shake vigorously. Strain into a chilled rocks glass over fresh ice. Hold a spoon with its back side facing up on the surface of the drink and slowly pour the ros\'e9 over it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf0 Yield: 1 drink.\
