\f0\fs52 \cf0 Spellbinder\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\ql\qnatural

\fs42 \cf0 This aromatic summer spin on the traditional gin martini takes its vivid hue from Strega, an Italian liqueur infused with saffron. For an added aesthetic boost, try garnishing with a long curl of cucumber cut with a vegetable peeler.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs38 \cf0 2 ounces gin\
1/2 ounce dry vermouth\
1/4 ounce Strega\
1 lemon peel strip, for garnish\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 1 cucumber strip (a long ribbon made with a vegetable peeler), for garnish.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\b\fs42 \cf0 Preparation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs38 \cf0 Combine the gin, vermouth and Strega in a cocktail shaker. Fill with ice and stir well until cold. Strain into a chilled coupe, add the lemon and cucumber and serve.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Yield: 1 drink.\
