\f0\fs52 \cf0 Italia Libera\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\ql\qnatural

\fs42 \cf0 The mixologist Chaim Dauermann wanted to tweak the Cuba Libre, a classic rum-and-Coke highball, without using cola, so he reached instead for a pungent white rum with hints of vanilla and paired it with bittersweet Italian amaro.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs38 \cf0 1 ounce overproof (150 proof alcohol) white rum\
1 ounce amaro\
1/4 ounce lemon juice\
3/4 ounce {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/22/dining/simple-syrup-recipe.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simple syrup}}\
Chilled seltzer\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 1 lime wedge, for garnish.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\b\fs42 \cf0 Preparation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs38 \cf0 Combine the rum, amaro, lemon juice and simple syrup in a cocktail shaker, fill with ice and shake vigorously. Strain into a highball glass over fresh ice, top with seltzer and garnish with the lime wedge.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Yield: 1 drink.\

