\f0\fs52 \cf0 Cherry Caipirissima\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\ql\qnatural

\fs44 \cf0 This seasonal spin on the Brazilian caipirinha demands vigorous shaking to break up the ice cubes and to give the finished drink a breezy, almost effervescent zip.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs40 \cf0 3/4 ounce {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/22/dining/simple-syrup-recipe.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simple syrup}}\
3 cherries, pitted and halved\
Half a lime, cut into quarters\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 2 ounces white rum.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\b\fs44 \cf0 Preparation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs40 \cf0 In a cocktail shaker, press and mix the simple syrup, cherries and lime quarters with a muddler or wooden spoon. Add the rum and 6 ice cubes. Shake hard and pour everything into a rocks glass.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Yield: 1 drink.\

